Name: Ark Prism
Description:
Flying transport. Can load and unload units and control space and time. Can also deploy to create a power field. Only one can exist in battlefield.

Cannot attack.

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target area or follow the target unit. Moving units will not engage enemies.
Root.Name: Move

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to cancel all orders and stop moving.
Root.Name: Stop

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to stay where they are and attack enemies that are within range. Units will neither chase down enemies nor move to engage.
Root.Name: Hold Position

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to patrol between their current position and the target area. Units will attack enemies and move to engage nearby enemies.
Root.Name: Patrol

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target point, fighting nearby enemies along the way. Targeting a unit with the Attack command orders that it be attacked until it is destroyed.
Root.Name: Attack

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target area or follow the target unit. Scan-moving units will not engage enemies.
Root.Name: Scan Move

Root.Tooltip: Loads units into the Warp Prism's matrix.
Root.Name: Load

Root.Tooltip: Consumes Ark Prism's shields in 4.5 seconds, increases its movement speed by 150% and becomes cloaked, reducing spell damage by 75%.
Root.Name: Overfrequency Acceleration

Root.Tooltip:
Gain 50% movement speed, and last 4.5 seconds. During this period, this skill was replaced with "Overfrequency Acceleration".

Overfrequency Acceleration: Ark Prism becomes cloaked and gains movement speed at the cost of shields.
Root.Name: Overfrequency Resonance

Root.Tooltip: Transforms to Phasing Mode and unlocks more abilities. During this period, Ark Prism will gain 50% vision range, and will become cloaked when loaded with units.
Root.Name: Phasing Mode

Root.Tooltip: Let Ark Prism blink to target location immediately.
Root.Name: Back to the Future

Root.Tooltip:
Leaves a static remnant in place, and the Ark Prism will return to that location after 10 seconds, restoring life and shields to its previous state. During this period, this skill was replaced with "Back to the Future".

Back to the Future: Ark Prism will blink to target location immediately.
Root.Name: Paradox Engine

Root.Tooltip: Unit unloaded will gain a barrier that will block 50 damage.
Root.Name: Sheltered Soul

Root.Tooltip:
After Slaughter and Blood Hunter are unloaded, their next attack can directly use the special weapons "Destruction Beam" and "Death Harvest".
These special weapons can also be used to target air and ground units while they are loaded in Ark Prism, and gain 1 additional weapon range, but attack speed is reduced by 100%.
Root.Name: Soul Forge

Root.Tooltip: Ark Prism will always maintain a certain distance from the enemy unit.
Root.Name: Repulsive Field

Root.Tooltip: Ark Prism can be upgraded to Crimson Space when it is in Phase Mode.
Root.Name: Transform Into Crimson Space

Root.Tooltip: Upon taking fatal damage, Ark Prism becomes immune to damage, but will be unable to move for 3 seconds.
Root.Name: Parallel Dimension

Behaviors.Tooltip: This unit can detect cloaked or burrowed units within its sight range.
Behaviors.Name: Detector
